@Akhilsnaik , actually sending empty array when there are no such hosts/components/services etc. is an architectural decision in Ambari, because that has some information content.
You can find such behaviour in many places in the code.
The python code must handle these cases properly, like the way you have suggested.

> @virajjasani What i mean is that "Peer cluster id" value should be verified in the ruby script, that it is indeed id and not something else.

@hapylestat One question: you mean we should check whether id is int and not something else? 
I agree, we should check this.
